Ulf,

Something like that could probably be done.  The reason it is slow is 
that the algorithm uses a full, nomerically-computed Jacobian. This 
means that all reactors in a network are assumed to be strongly coupled 
to one another.  For many networks, this is not the case, and the 
Jacobian is actually sparse.  Modifying the Jacobian evaluation 
procedures in CVODE to take advantage of the structure of the Jacobian 
would probably go a long way toward boosting speed.

Dave


